The paper deals with action detection in videos, which is a common problem in computer vision. The use of attention models and weakly-supervised learning also suggests a focus on machine learning and deep learning techniques, which are often found in the computer science sub-categories of computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), multimedia (cs.MM), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and information retrieval (cs.IR).
